Mozilla Mexico web template for slides

To generate a new slides all you have to do is modify the index.html and style.css for content and look and feel.

Transitions are in transitions.js and the core of animation are in script.js.

for example:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Title</title>
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Signika+Negative' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css" />
    <script src="./transitions.js"></script>
    <script src="./script.js"></script>
</head>
<body onload="init();" onkeydown="keyDetect(event);">
    <section style="display:none;" data-transition-in="twister">
        <div class="container">
            <img src="mozmex_gris.png" alt="" />
        </div>
    </section>
    <section style="display:none;" data-transition-in="zoomIn">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="title">Title</h1>
        </div>
    </section>
</body>
</html>

oslides just support right now to transitions:

* twister
* zoomIn

for add a new slide just need:

<section data-transition-in="transition">
    <div container>
        Content
    </div>
</section>

